1
00:00:57,413 --> 00:00:59,707
给我点空间 这下好了
All right, give me room. Here we go.

2
00:01:13,971 --> 00:01:16,265
- 这个游戏叫什么名字？ - 轻型摩托
- What's this game called? - This is Lightcycle.

3
00:01:32,156 --> 00:01:33,824
见鬼！
Damn.

4
00:01:50,215 --> 00:01:52,843
你正变得更加野蛮 萨克
You're getting brutal, Sark.

5
00:01:52,843 --> 00:01:55,095
无谓的残酷成性
Brutal and needlessly sadistic.

6
00:01:55,095 --> 00:01:57,681
谢谢 主控制
Thank you, Master Control.

7
00:01:57,681 --> 00:02:00,684
我们截获了一些军事程序
We have kidnapped some military programs.

8
00:02:00,684 --> 00:02:03,354
我可以安排更多的致命比赛
I can arrange more lethal matches.

9
00:02:03,354 --> 00:02:05,606
- 有兴趣吗？ - 当然
- Interested? - Sure.

10
00:02:05,606 --> 00:02:08,192
我很乐意和他们中的一位比比
I'd love to go up against one of those guys.

11
00:02:08,192 --> 00:02:13,113
从那些会计泡沫程序中中断一个给我
It'd make a nice break from those accounting cream puffs you keep sending me.

12
00:02:13,113 --> 00:02:17,451
- 是什么分支？ - 战略空军指令
- What branch of the service? - Strategic Air Command.

13
00:02:17,451 --> 00:02:19,453
很好！
Nice.

14
00:02:19,453 --> 00:02:23,207
听着 这完全是一场误会
Hey, look. This is all a mistake.

15
00:02:23,207 --> 00:02:25,501
我只是一个复合利息程序
I am just a compound interest program.

16
00:02:25,501 --> 00:02:28,962
我的工作是储蓄和借贷 我无法玩那些电视游戏
I work at a savings and loan. I can't play these video games.

17
00:02:28,962 --> 00:02:32,466
你当然可以 你看上去像一个天生的运动员
Sure you can, pal. You look like a natural athlete if I ever saw one.

18
00:02:32,466 --> 00:02:34,468
谁 我吗？你在开玩笑？
Who, me? Are you kidding?

19
00:02:34,468 --> 00:02:37,554
我正在核算短期国库券利率 我只是出来透口气
I went out to check on T-bill rates, I get out of breath.

20
00:02:37,554 --> 00:02:40,808
你们这样会让我的用户亨德森先生非常生气
Hey, look. You guys are going to make my User, Mr. Henderson, very angry.

21
00:02:40,808 --> 00:02:44,853
- 他可是一个完整分支机构的经理 - 很好 另一个宗教狂热
- He's a full branch manager. - Great. Another religious nut.

22
00:02:48,399 --> 00:02:52,319
我应该说“欢迎 朋友” 但不是在这里 不象这样
I'd say, "Welcome, friend", but not here, not like this.

23
00:02:52,319 --> 00:02:54,530
我不知道自己怎么会到这里的
I don't even know what I am doing here.

24
00:02:56,782 --> 00:02:59,701
你是存在于“用户”系统中的吗？
Do you believe in the Users?

25
00:02:59,701 --> 00:03:03,330
那当然了 如果没有用户 谁写了我？
Yeah, sure. If I don't have a User, then who wrote me?

26
00:03:03,330 --> 00:03:05,332
那就是为什么你会在这里的原因
That's what you're doing here.

27
00:03:05,332 --> 00:03:09,378
主控制程序夺取了我们这些程序
Master Control Program's been snapping up all us programs who believe.

28
00:03:09,378 --> 00:03:12,464
如果你是有用的 他就夺取你所有的功能而变得更强大
If he thinks you're useful, he takes over all your functions so he gets bigger.

29
00:03:12,464 --> 00:03:16,844
如果他不能利用你 就送你到这里来受苦
If he can't use you, he sends you down here to the game grid get your bits blasted.

30
00:03:16,844 --> 00:03:19,721
- 你叫什么名字？ - 克罗姆
- What's your name? - Crom.

31
00:03:19,721 --> 00:03:22,224
我是拉姆
I am Ram.

32
00:03:22,224 --> 00:03:24,435
他们会训练你来玩这个游戏
They will train you for the games, but...

33
00:03:24,435 --> 00:03:28,397
但是… 我希望你能做到
I hope you make it.

34
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:32,067
别的部门变成什么样了？
Hey, what's been going on in the other sectors?

35
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:34,695
我已经被关在这200个周期了
I have been stuck here for 200 microcycles.

36
00:03:36,446 --> 00:03:38,365
外面简直是在谋杀
It's murder out there.

37
00:03:38,365 --> 00:03:40,784
没有主控制程序的允许…
You can't even travel around in your own microcircuits...

38
00:03:40,784 --> 00:03:44,663
你无法进入自己的微电路
without permission from Master Control Program.

39
00:03:44,663 --> 00:03:46,999
把我送到这里来玩游戏
I mean, sending me down here to play games.

40
00:03:46,999 --> 00:03:49,293
他认为自己是谁啊？
Who does he calculate he is?

41
00:03:51,005 --> 00:03:52,555
真实世界的同时


42
00:03:55,299 --> 00:03:57,217
好吧 克鲁
Okay, Clu,

43
00:03:57,217 --> 00:03:59,678
今天我们来检查所有右手列的数据
tonight we check everything in the right-hand column.

44
00:04:02,139 --> 00:04:05,058
来吧 来吧 你在哪里？
Come on. Come on. Where are you?

45
00:04:05,058 --> 00:04:07,060
- 你在这里 克鲁？ - 是的 先生
- There you are. Clu? - Yes, sir.

46
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:09,730
这次我要你仔细找到那些文件 这是首要的
We don't have much time to find that file. This is top priority.

47
00:04:09,730 --> 00:04:11,732
- 我知道 先生 - 这次不是仅仅校正我的银行报表…
- I know, sir. - This isn't correcting my bank statement...

48
00:04:11,732 --> 00:04:13,734
或电话账单… 这次是完全控制
or phone bill problem... this is a must.

49
00:04:13,734 --> 00:04:15,736
- 我明白 - 我写了你
- I understand. - Now, I wrote you.

50
00:04:15,736 --> 00:04:17,738
- 是的 先生 - 我告诉了你关于系统所有的一切
- Yes, sir. - I taught you everything about the system.

51
00:04:17,738 --> 00:04:20,532
- 谢谢 但是… - 没有但是 那是为了用户
- Thank you, but... - No buts. That's for Users.

52
00:04:20,532 --> 00:04:22,576
你是最好的程序
You're the best program that's ever been written.

53
00:04:22,576 --> 00:04:24,786
- 你是顽固无情的 记得吗？ - 让我瞄准他们
- You're dogged and relentless, remember? - Let me at them.

54
00:04:24,786 --> 00:04:27,247
那是精神 让坦克动起来
That's the spirit. Keep that tank rolling.

55
00:04:27,247 --> 00:04:29,750
我会在这里掩护你 快走
I will try to cover you from this end. Go.

56
00:04:48,769 --> 00:04:51,438
你认为我们可以融入这些数据流吗？
You think we can merge with this memory, Bit?

57
00:04:52,521 --> 00:04:53,482
是的
Yes.

58
00:05:01,406 --> 00:05:03,659
弗林说检查这边
Now Flynn is saying to look over in here,

59
00:05:03,659 --> 00:05:05,869
我没有看见我们所要看的
but I don't see what we're looking for.

60
00:05:12,918 --> 00:05:16,296
快点 那些鬼数据就在那里
Come on, you scuzzy data, be in there. Come on.

61
00:05:23,136 --> 00:05:26,973
我们有伙伴了
We have got company.

62
00:05:31,728 --> 00:05:33,814
我不能相信这个
I don't believe this.

63
00:05:33,814 --> 00:05:37,359
- 一个识别器 - 是 是 是 是 是
- A Recognizer. - Yes-yes-yes-yes-yes.

64
00:05:49,079 --> 00:05:50,580
他们太多了！
There's too many.

65
00:06:11,935 --> 00:06:14,396
这是什么？
What is this?

66
00:06:30,954 --> 00:06:32,372
见鬼！
Damn it.

67
00:06:37,461 --> 00:06:41,465
- 快离开 - 是 是 是
- Get out of here. - Yes-yes-yes.

68
00:06:38,935 --> 00:06:40,856
是 是 是
Yes-yes-yes.

69
00:06:53,476 --> 00:06:55,729
又失败了！
Busted again.

70
00:06:55,729 --> 00:06:59,900
那是我最好的程序
God, and that was my best program.

71
00:07:09,659 --> 00:07:13,413
抓到了一个非法程序 自称他的名字叫克鲁
Got a pirate program here. Says his name's Clu.

72
00:07:13,413 --> 00:07:15,415
他想要什么？
What did he pull?

73
00:07:15,415 --> 00:07:18,418
他通过一个被盗密码进入系统
He came into the system with a stolen password.

74
00:07:18,418 --> 00:07:21,421
我们发现他试图进入高级内存
We caught him trying to raid our high-clearance memory.

75
00:07:21,421 --> 00:07:24,841
不！ 我一定是不小心到那里的
No. I must have gotten in there by mistake.

76
00:07:24,841 --> 00:07:27,844
- 谁编写了你？ - 我只是简单…
- Who programmed you? - I was simp...

77
00:07:36,102 --> 00:07:38,021
你有麻烦了 程序
You're in trouble, program.

78
00:07:38,021 --> 00:07:41,232
让自己舒服点吧 谁是你的用户？
Make it easy on yourself. Who's your User?

79
00:07:41,232 --> 00:07:44,486
忘了他吧 强大的主控制先生
Forget it, Mr. High And Mighty Master Control.

80
00:07:46,780 --> 00:07:48,865
你无法让我说的
You aren't making me talk.

81
00:07:51,117 --> 00:07:53,244
当心自己
Suit yourself.

82
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:08,593
替我找迪林杰
Get me Dillinger.

83
00:09:00,186 --> 00:09:02,397
晚上好 迪林杰先生
Good evening, Mr. Dillinger.

84
00:09:02,397 --> 00:09:04,399
谢谢 皮特 你可以走了
Thank you, Peter. You can go now.

85
00:09:04,399 --> 00:09:06,443
是的 先生
Yes, sir.

86
00:09:16,904 --> 00:09:26,125
要求接通主控制程序 用户代码00-迪林杰 密码：MASTER


87
00:09:27,906 --> 00:09:30,507
你好 迪林杰先生 谢谢尽早回来


88
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:32,969
没问题 主控制
No problem, Master C.

89
00:09:32,969 --> 00:09:36,222
如果你看了一个电子展览 你就等于看了全部
If you have seen one consumer electronics show, you have seen them all.

90
00:09:36,222 --> 00:09:38,224
怎么啦？
What's up?

91
00:09:38,224 --> 00:09:40,852
那是你的朋友-身体检查 又在折腾了


92
00:09:40,852 --> 00:09:42,896
- 弗林？ - 是的
- Flynn? - Yes.

93
00:09:44,647 --> 00:09:47,775
他仍然在找那些老文件 你没办法处理吗？
He's still looking for that old file. Can't you just appropriate it?

94
00:09:47,775 --> 00:09:51,696
我有 我把它放到他还不知道的内存中
I have. I put it in my memory, which he hasn't located.

95
00:09:51,696 --> 00:09:55,366
- 他有可能找到它 - 恐怕是的
- But he might find it. - I am afraid so.

96
00:09:55,366 --> 00:09:57,994
这次我阻止了他并把他踢了出去 但他变得越来越狡猾
I spotted him this time and kept him out,

97
00:09:57,994 --> 00:10:01,289
它变得越来越麻烦了
but he's getting trickier all the time.

98
00:10:01,289 --> 00:10:03,750
我们应该关闭所有入口…
I think we should shut down all access...

99
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,127
直到我们找到那个弗林 仅为安全起见
until we find that Flynn, just to be safe.

100
00:10:06,127 --> 00:10:11,299
- 你有68.71%的机会是正确的 - 聪明
- There's a 68.71% chance you're right. - Cute.

101
00:10:11,514 --> 00:10:12,514
结束


102
00:10:17,515 --> 00:10:21,516
要求的文件为空… 创程序不可用


103
00:10:23,516 --> 00:10:34,518
要求：主控制释放程序创 JA 307020…
我有优先接入权力7


104
00:10:43,039 --> 00:10:44,958
- 你的接入被暂停 请立即找迪林杰先生 - 见鬼！


105
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:49,128
艾伦 我能吃些你的爆米花吗？
Hey, Alan. You think I could have some of your popcorn?

106
00:10:49,128 --> 00:10:51,422
是的 当然
Yeah, sure.

107
00:11:20,994 --> 00:11:24,163
- 坐下 - 谢谢
- Sit down. - Thank you.

108
00:11:28,584 --> 00:11:30,920
我们不得不关闭所有第7级用户组
We have had to shut down all Group-7 personnel.

109
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:33,381
暂时的 为了安全
Just briefly. Security.

110
00:11:33,381 --> 00:11:35,717
有人暂时得到了我们的接入
Someone with that access has been tampering.

111
00:11:35,717 --> 00:11:38,344
你不会认为是我吧！
I hope you don't think it's me.

112
00:11:38,344 --> 00:11:40,430
停机期间我甚至无法平衡我的支票簿
I don't even balance my chequebook on downtime.

113
00:11:40,430 --> 00:11:43,516
- 我的家庭需要它 - 你一定可以理解
- I have an abacus at home for that. - I am sure you understand.

114
00:11:43,516 --> 00:11:46,853
只是几天而已 你正在做的项目是什么？
It will only be a couple of days. What's the project you're working on?

115
00:11:46,853 --> 00:11:51,357
它叫创 实际上它是个安全程序
It's called Tron. It's a security program itself, actually.

116
00:11:51,357 --> 00:11:55,445
它监视我们的系统和别人的联系
It monitors all contacts between our system and other systems.

117
00:11:55,445 --> 00:11:58,364
任何没有预定的 它就关闭它
Finds anything going on that's not scheduled, it shuts it down.

118
00:11:58,364 --> 00:12:01,159
我给你发过备忘
I sent you a memo on it.

119
00:12:01,159 --> 00:12:03,327
主控制程序的一部分？
Part of the Master Control Program?

120
00:12:03,327 --> 00:12:08,541
不是 它是独立运行的 同时也监视主控制程序
No, it will run independently and watchdog the MCP as well.

121
00:12:08,541 --> 00:12:11,919
听上去不错
Sounds good.

122
00:12:11,919 --> 00:12:15,339
我们应该可以在几天内让你恢复工作 但愿吧
We should have you running in a couple of days. I hope.

123
00:12:17,675 --> 00:12:18,925
好吧
Okay.

124
00:12:20,553 --> 00:12:22,555
谢谢
Thanks.

125
00:12:35,902 --> 00:12:37,820
孩子
Oh, boy.

126
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:40,948
迪林杰先生 我对你非常失望
Mr. Dillinger, I am so very disappointed in you.

127
00:12:40,948 --> 00:12:42,950
对不起
I am sorry.

128
00:12:42,950 --> 00:12:46,996
我不能负担一个独立的程序监视我
I can't afford to have an independent programmer monitoring me.

129
00:12:46,996 --> 00:12:50,208
你知道我要进入多少外部系统？
Do you realize how many outside systems I have gone into?

130
00:12:50,208 --> 00:12:52,502
多少程序我要处理？
How many programs I have appropriated?

131
00:12:53,544 --> 00:12:55,505
快点！
Come on.

132
00:12:56,631 --> 00:12:59,008
几天！
A couple of days.

133
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,278
你好 吉布斯博士
Hi, Dr. Gibbs.

134
00:13:32,131 --> 00:13:36,131
系统纪录 1039 主传送序列限制你的


135
00:13:50,059 --> 00:13:51,978
这里什么都没有
Well, here goes nothing.

136
00:13:51,978 --> 00:13:55,731
是的 有趣有趣 你知道你刚才说了什么？
Yeah, interesting. You hear what you just said?

137
00:13:55,731 --> 00:13:58,192
- “这里什么都没有” - 我是说…
- "Here goes nothing." - Well, what I meant was...

138
00:13:58,192 --> 00:14:02,571
实际上 我们计划要将一些东西变走 然后再变回来
Actually, what we propose to do is to change something into nothing and back again.

139
00:14:02,571 --> 00:14:06,659
你应该说“这里有些东西 这里变成没有东西”
You might just as well have said, "Here goes something, here comes nothing."

140
00:14:06,659 --> 00:14:11,122
- Right. - All right. Let's clear the area.

141
00:14:14,458 --> 00:14:16,377
这是关键时刻
This is the big moment.

142
00:14:16,377 --> 00:14:19,422
那将限制你的理论 U-V扫描电波…
I know. This will narrow your theory that the scanned U-V beam...

143
00:14:19,422 --> 00:14:21,924
应该是单脉冲传播
is superior to single pulse exposure.

144
00:14:21,924 --> 00:14:25,678
30秒内进行激光操作
Laser activity will exist in 30 seconds.

145
00:14:25,678 --> 00:14:28,556
戴上护目镜 离开这个隔间到安全区
Put on your goggles. Leave the bay.

146
00:14:28,556 --> 00:14:31,017
让我们看看我们是否得到了绿光
Let's see if we have got the green light.

147
00:14:31,017 --> 00:14:34,145
- 目标区域隔离了？ - 他们确认安全
- Is the target area shielded? - They verified safety.

148
00:14:34,145 --> 00:14:36,731
20 秒
Twenty seconds.

149
00:14:36,731 --> 00:14:39,525
- 看上去不错 - 让她干吧
- Looks good. - Let her rip.

150
00:14:39,525 --> 00:14:41,569
这正是我们在等待的
This is what we have been waiting for.

151
00:14:42,945 --> 00:14:45,573
10 秒
Ten seconds.

152
00:14:48,617 --> 00:14:52,580
5 秒
Five seconds.

153
00:15:07,261 --> 00:15:08,221
完美！
Perfect.

154
00:15:10,639 --> 00:15:13,434
- 棒极了 - 你好 艾伦
- Beautiful. - Hi, Alan.

155
00:15:13,434 --> 00:15:16,395
分解物体很有趣？
You two having fun disintegrating things?

156
00:15:16,395 --> 00:15:18,731
不是分解 是数字化
Not disintegrating, digitizing.

157
00:15:18,731 --> 00:15:22,526
一束激光拆除分子结构
A laser dismantles the molecular structure of the object,

158
00:15:22,526 --> 00:15:25,988
分子暂时保存在激光束中
and molecules remain suspended in the laser beam.

159
00:15:25,988 --> 00:15:28,574
当电脑计算出模型
Then, when the computer plays out the model,

160
00:15:28,574 --> 00:15:32,077
分子回到原位 瞧？
the molecules fall back into place, and voil?

161
00:15:32,077 --> 00:15:34,413
很棒 它能把我送到夏威夷吗？
Great. Can it send me to Hawaii?

162
00:15:34,413 --> 00:15:39,335
你必须提前30天购买你的程序
Yeah, but you have got to purchase your program 30 days in advance.

163
00:15:39,335 --> 00:15:41,462
楼上怎么样？
How's it going upstairs?

164
00:15:41,462 --> 00:15:45,257
令人灰心 我的创就快成功了…
Frustrating. I had Tron almost ready...

165
00:15:45,257 --> 00:15:48,594
就当迪林杰关闭所有第7级接入时
when Dillinger cut everyone with Group-7 access out of the system.

166
00:15:48,594 --> 00:15:52,807
从他有了那个主控制程序后
Ever since he got that Master Control Program,

167
00:15:52,807 --> 00:15:55,392
系统里的虫子比诱饵商店还多
the system's got more bugs than a bait store.

168
00:15:55,392 --> 00:15:57,394
你犯了些错误
You got to expect some static.

169
00:15:57,394 --> 00:16:00,272
计算机只是机器 它们不会思考
After all, computers are just machines. They can't think.

170
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:02,274
一些程序很快就要会思考了
Some programs will be thinking soon.

171
00:16:02,274 --> 00:16:04,610
不觉得很宏大吗？
Won't that be grand?

172
00:16:04,610 --> 00:16:08,447
计算机如果会思考 人类就不会思考了
Computers and programs will start thinking, and the people will stop.

173
00:16:08,447 --> 00:16:11,116
我要留下来 去输入些数据 明天见
I am going to stay around, put some data through. See you tomorrow.

174
00:16:11,116 --> 00:16:12,116
再见
Bye.

175
00:16:13,369 --> 00:16:15,621
来吧
Come on.

176
00:16:15,621 --> 00:16:18,832
- 你是说第7级接入组吗？ - 是的
- Did you say Group-7 access? - Yeah.

177
00:16:18,832 --> 00:16:22,127
真是混蛋 我都准备好了
What a hassle. I was all set.

178
00:16:22,127 --> 00:16:25,339
- 他有说为什么吗？ - 关于什么篡改的事情
- Did he say why? - Something about tampering.

179
00:16:26,382 --> 00:16:28,300
篡改？
Tampering?

180
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:32,179
自从迪林杰解雇了他 弗林一直试图闯入系统
Flynn has been thinking about breaking into the system ever since Dillinger canned him.

181
00:16:32,179 --> 00:16:34,390
而且他有第7级接入权限
And he had Group-7 access.

182
00:16:34,390 --> 00:16:37,393
弗林也有进入你的权限
Flynn had access to you too.

183
00:16:40,646 --> 00:16:42,565
我想去弗林那里
I want to go to Flynn's place.

184
00:16:42,565 --> 00:16:44,567
- 干吗？ - 警告他
- What for? - To warn him.

185
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:48,988
- 警告什么？ - 迪林杰在注意他
- Of what? - That Dillinger's onto him.

186
00:16:48,988 --> 00:16:52,491
我不知道我为什么要帮助他！
I don't see why I have to do that guy any favors.

187
00:16:52,491 --> 00:16:54,994
我不知道你到底看上他哪点
I don't know what you ever saw in that guy, anyway.

188
00:16:54,994 --> 00:16:58,664
我爱他的头脑
I loved him for his brains.

189
00:16:58,664 --> 00:17:02,126
别把零钱放入计价器 我们需要它们打游戏
Don't put any change in the meter. We're going to need it for the games.

190
00:17:07,756 --> 00:17:09,842
孩子 我好久没来这里了
Boy. I haven't been here in a long time.

191
00:17:18,976 --> 00:17:21,353
伙计 这里
Hey, Bobby, up here.

192
00:17:44,001 --> 00:17:46,211
- 他在哪里？ - 我不知道
- Where is he? - I don't know.

193
00:17:46,211 --> 00:17:48,547
迷失在他的某个游戏中
Somewhere in here, lost in one of his games.

194
00:17:54,136 --> 00:17:56,388
你知道弗林在哪里吗？
Excuse me. Do you know where Flynn is?

195
00:17:56,388 --> 00:17:58,390
知道 就在他的机器边
Yeah, he's over there on his machine.

196
00:18:06,106 --> 00:18:08,859
他正在操纵 又一个纪录
He's really on a roll. One more Reco before he ties.

197
00:18:08,859 --> 00:18:12,988
又一个纪录 他破了世界纪录
Another Reco and he gets the world's record.

198
00:18:22,498 --> 00:18:26,502
他要破纪录了 所有的纪录
He's going for the record. The all-time record coming up.

199
00:18:30,839 --> 00:18:33,634
就是它了 结束了
This is it. It's all over.

200
00:18:36,011 --> 00:18:38,806
弗林这把他自己变成历史的一部分！
Flynn's going to be a part of history, all right.

201
00:18:43,602 --> 00:18:45,521
弗林 你怎么做到的？
Hey, Flynn, how'd you do it?

202
00:18:45,521 --> 00:18:48,607
全靠手腕
It's all in the wrists.

203
00:18:48,607 --> 00:18:51,360
999,000点！
999,000 points.

204
00:18:53,862 --> 00:18:56,490
见到你们真高兴
Hey, good to see you guys.

205
00:18:56,490 --> 00:18:59,576
Nothing classes up the joint like a clean-cut young couple.

206
00:18:59,576 --> 00:19:01,620
我们得谈谈
We got to talk.

207
00:19:01,620 --> 00:19:03,747
在这里听不见你自己 来吧
You can't hear yourself think in here. Come on.

208
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:08,544
- 来吧 - 我离开一会儿
- Come on. - I will be down in a minute.

209
00:19:10,379 --> 00:19:12,464
严肃科学的世界怎么样了？
How's the world of serious science?

210
00:19:12,464 --> 00:19:14,466
就象在家里一样
Go up ahead. Make yourselves at home.

211
00:19:14,466 --> 00:19:16,635
一直等着
Be right up.

212
00:19:19,513 --> 00:19:23,392
英康曾见过的最好的程序员
The best programmer ENCOM ever saw,

213
00:19:23,392 --> 00:19:27,813
而他正在屋子里玩太空牛仔
and he winds up playing space cowboy in some back room.

214
00:19:27,813 --> 00:19:29,815
让我来说
Okay, let me handle this.

215
00:19:29,815 --> 00:19:31,900
说吧
Go right ahead.

216
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:35,362
你有没有偷入英康系统？
Have you been sneaking into the ENCOM system?

217
00:19:37,406 --> 00:19:40,075
你从没有很多闲聊
You never were much for small talk, were you?

218
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:45,080
她是否还是把她的衣服扔得到处都是？没有
She still leave her clothes all over the floor? No.

219
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:48,166
- 艾伦 - 我的意思是没那么经常
- Alan. - I mean, not that often.

220
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,419
你现在明白为什么他的朋友都只有14岁了
You can see why all his friends are 14 years old.

221
00:19:50,419 --> 00:19:51,259
接触？
Touch?

222
00:20:02,347 --> 00:20:04,683
实际上我有做过一些黑客
I have been doing a little hacking, as a matter of fact.

223
00:20:04,683 --> 00:20:07,436
- 你确实闯入 - 尝试
- You did break in. - Tried to.

224
00:20:07,436 --> 00:20:11,064
我看上去不能很好的连接
I can't seem to quite get the connection with that sucker, though.

225
00:20:11,064 --> 00:20:13,191
如果我有一个直接的终端…
If I had a direct terminal...

226
00:20:13,191 --> 00:20:15,193
弗林 你有没有侵吞？
Flynn, are you embezzling?

227
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:20,866
侵吞是一个丑陋的词 布拉德利先生
Embezzling is such an ugly word, Mr. Bradley.

228
00:20:20,866 --> 00:20:23,952
实际上 我正在尝试找些证据
No, actually, I am trying to get some solid evidence together.

229
00:20:23,952 --> 00:20:28,206
- 我不明白 - 好吧
- I don't get it. - Okay.

230
00:20:28,206 --> 00:20:33,086
让我们回到三年前
Sherman, set the Way-Back Machine for three years ago.

231
00:20:33,086 --> 00:20:35,380
凯文・弗林
Kevin Flynn,

232
00:20:35,380 --> 00:20:39,760
英康最聪明的年轻软件工程师
one of ENCOM's brightest young software engineers.

233
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:42,387
他是如此聪明 在晚上他开始工作
He's so bright, he starts going in at night,

234
00:20:42,387 --> 00:20:44,389
建立他自己的私人记忆文档…
sets up his own private memory file...

235
00:20:44,389 --> 00:20:48,727
并开始写一个电视游戏 叫做…
and begins writing a program for video games, invented called...

236
00:20:48,727 --> 00:20:50,896
“太空妄想者”
Space Paranoids.

237
00:20:50,896 --> 00:20:53,398
你写了“太空妄想者”？
You invented Space Paranoids?

238
00:20:53,398 --> 00:20:57,069
“妄想者” “矩阵爆破工” “警察缉捕队” 一系列的
Paranoids, Matrix Blaster, Vice Squad... a whole slew of them.

239
00:20:57,069 --> 00:20:59,654
我离自己的事业就差这一小步
I was this close to starting my own little enterprise.

240
00:20:59,654 --> 00:21:03,575
但是进来了另一个软件工程师
But enter another software engineer;

241
00:21:03,575 --> 00:21:06,745
不是那么年轻聪明的 但是非常非常卑鄙;
not so young, not so bright, but very, very sneaky;

242
00:21:06,745 --> 00:21:09,372
Ed・迪林杰
Ed Dillinger.

243
00:21:09,372 --> 00:21:10,470
一个夜晚 我们的男孩弗林
One night, our boy Flynn,

244
00:21:10,470 --> 00:21:11,568
进入他的终端
he goes to his terminal,

245
00:21:11,568 --> 00:21:12,667
试图读取他的文件
tries to read up his file.

246
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:16,004
我什么也没读到 那儿一片空白
I get nothing on there. There's a big blank.

247
00:21:16,004 --> 00:21:18,090
好吧 现在我们带你到3个月后
All right, now we take you three months later,

248
00:21:18,090 --> 00:21:21,968
迪林杰发布了英康的5个电视游戏…
Dillinger presents ENCOM with five video games...

249
00:21:21,968 --> 00:21:23,970
都是他开发的
that he's invented.

250
00:21:23,970 --> 00:21:26,306
这人渣甚至没有改名字
The slime didn't even change the names, man.

251
00:21:26,306 --> 00:21:28,308
他得到了大提升
He gets a big, fat promotion.

252
00:21:28,308 --> 00:21:31,144
然后开始了他流星般的升迁至…他现在是什么？
Thus begins his meteoric rise to... what is he now?

253
00:21:31,144 --> 00:21:34,439
- 执行副总裁？ - 高级执行官？
- Executive V.P? - Senior exec?

254
00:21:34,439 --> 00:21:36,691
高级执行官？
Senior exec?

255
00:21:39,486 --> 00:21:42,134
期间 孩子们一个星期投了8百万2角5分
Meanwhile, kids are putting eight million 

256
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,783
辅币到幻想者机器中
quarters a week into Paranoid machines.

257
00:21:44,783 --> 00:21:47,786
我没有看见一角钱 除了从这儿榨到的
I don't see a dime, except what I squeeze out of here.

258
00:21:47,786 --> 00:21:51,957
我仍然不理解你为什么要闯入系统
I still don't understand why you want to break into the system.

259
00:21:51,957 --> 00:21:56,837
内存中的某个地方有证据
Because, man, somewhere in one of these memories is the evidence.

260
00:21:56,837 --> 00:21:59,965
如果我能进入的足够远 我可以重组它
If I got in far enough I could reconstruct it.

261
00:21:59,965 --> 00:22:02,968
我的密码 迪林杰的转移指令…
My password, Dillinger's instructions to divert the data...

262
00:22:02,968 --> 00:22:07,138
太晚了 迪林杰已经关闭了第7级组接入权限
It's too late for that. Dillinger's cut off everybody with Group-7 access.

263
00:22:07,138 --> 00:22:09,641
等等 你说什么？
Wait. Wait. What are you saying?

264
00:22:09,641 --> 00:22:12,811
这家伙知道你要什么
The guy knows what you're up to.

265
00:22:12,811 --> 00:22:15,897
太棒了 你在跟我开玩笑？
Great. You're kidding me?

266
00:22:18,859 --> 00:22:22,445
现在什么都不能阻止他
Well, now there is nothing to stop him.

267
00:22:22,445 --> 00:22:26,825
现在只有迪林杰和主控制程序运行一切
It's just Dillinger and the MCP running things from on high now.

268
00:22:26,825 --> 00:22:30,912
如果我的创程序在运行就不会了 那会关了系统
Not if my Tron program was running. That'd shut the system down.

269
00:22:35,292 --> 00:22:37,210
如果你的文件在那里…
You know, if your file was in there...

270
00:22:37,210 --> 00:22:39,296
等等 如果我们可以到那里
Wait a minute. If we can get in there,

271
00:22:39,296 --> 00:22:41,673
我可以伪造一个第6级接入
I can forge us a Group-6 access.

272
00:22:42,799 --> 00:22:46,928
好吧？我们应该跳舞了吗？
Well? Shall we dance?

273
00:22:56,146 --> 00:22:58,857
我有很好的理由关闭第7级接入
I shut down Group-7 for a very good reason.

274
00:22:58,857 --> 00:23:03,028
如果我们的人不能接入他们的程序…
Ed, all I am saying is if our people can't get access to their programs...

275
00:23:03,028 --> 00:23:06,197
你知道这令他们多灰心吗？
Well, you know how frustrating it is when you're working on a piece of research.

276
00:23:06,197 --> 00:23:09,868
我很同情 但主控制程序告诉我
I sympathize, but I have data coming from the Master Control Program...

277
00:23:09,868 --> 00:23:12,245
那里有些不对劲
telling me there's something screwy going on.

278
00:23:12,245 --> 00:23:14,914
那个主控制程序是所有问题的一半！
That MCP, that's half our problem right there.

279
00:23:14,914 --> 00:23:18,084
主控制程序是最有效管理我们工作的方式！
The MCP is the most efficient way of handling what we do.

280
00:23:18,084 --> 00:23:21,296
我不能坐在这里照顾每个用户的请求
I can't sit here and worry about every little User request that comes in.

281
00:23:21,296 --> 00:23:23,590
用户请求是电脑在这里的目的
User requests are what computers are for.

282
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:26,343
做我们的生意是电脑在这里的目的！
Doing our business is what computers are for.

283
00:23:44,569 --> 00:23:47,614
英康不再是你的车库中发起的生意了
ENCOM isn't the business you started in your garage any more.

284
00:23:47,614 --> 00:23:51,242
我们在30个国家有机构
We're building accounts in 30 different countries, new defense systems.

285
00:23:51,242 --> 00:23:54,329
新的防御系统中最长久的部分
We have one of the most sophisticated pieces of equipment in existence.

286
00:23:54,329 --> 00:23:56,373
这些我都知道
Oh, I know all that.

287
00:23:57,999 --> 00:24:01,419
有时我希望回到自己的车库
Sometimes I wish I were back in that garage.

288
00:24:01,419 --> 00:24:03,755
那可以安排 沃尔特
That can be arranged, Walter.

289
00:24:05,382 --> 00:24:07,300
那是没有理由的
That was uncalled for.

290
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:11,429
你可以开除艾伦和我 但我们协助创造了它
You can remove men like Alan and me from the system, but we helped create it.

291
00:24:11,429 --> 00:24:15,767
我们的精神会留在每一个我们设计的程序中
And our spirit remains in every program we designed for this computer.

292
00:24:15,767 --> 00:24:18,103
沃尔特 很晚了 我有更好的事情要做…
Walter, it's getting late. I have got better things to do...

293
00:24:18,103 --> 00:24:20,313
不跟你做无谓的讨论
than to have religious discussions with you.

294
00:24:20,313 --> 00:24:24,943
不必再担心英康 现在超出你的掌握了
Don't worry about ENCOM any more. It's out of your hands now.

295
00:24:33,201 --> 00:24:35,620
我不认为我有授权
I don't think I am cleared for this.

296
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:37,747
- 我当然也没有 - 能站开些吗？
- I am certainly not. - You want to move aside?

297
00:24:37,747 --> 00:24:40,083
给我点小小空间
Give the kid a little room.

298
00:24:43,628 --> 00:24:45,630
这家伙有点象圣诞老人
This guy's a little like Santa Claus.

299
00:24:47,298 --> 00:24:49,217
我自己做的 你要一个吗？
I make these myself. You want one?

300
00:25:01,062 --> 00:25:03,481
他们不应该开除我
They never should have gotten rid of me.

301
00:25:06,985 --> 00:25:09,863
- 现在他是一扇大门了 - 闭嘴
- Now that is a big door. - Shut up.

302
00:25:19,247 --> 00:25:21,666
那是我的错 我设计你想要得太多了
It's my fault. I programmed you to want too much.

303
00:25:21,666 --> 00:25:24,168
我正准备攻击五角大楼
I was planning to hit the Pentagon next week.

304
00:25:24,168 --> 00:25:26,337
五角大楼？
The Pentagon?

305
00:25:26,337 --> 00:25:29,340
那应该不会比任何大公司难
It shouldn't be harder than any other big company.

306
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:32,343
这是我从人类这里学到的
But now this is what I get for using humans.

307
00:25:32,343 --> 00:25:34,596
等一下 我写了你
Wait a minute. I wrote you.

308
00:25:34,596 --> 00:25:38,933
我比那时聪明了2.45百万倍
I have gotten 2,415 times smarter since then.

309
00:25:38,933 --> 00:25:41,311
你想从五角大楼得到什么？
What do you want with the Pentagon?

310
00:25:41,311 --> 00:25:45,356
和我想从克林姆林宫得到的一样 我对公司很反感
The same thing I want with the Kremlin. I am bored with corporations.

311
00:25:45,356 --> 00:25:48,359
有了这些信息 我可以进入
With the information I can access,

312
00:25:48,359 --> 00:25:52,822
我可以比任何人运行的好900到1200倍
I can run things 900 to 1,200 times better than any human.

313
00:25:52,822 --> 00:25:55,283
如果你认为你超越了我们…
If you think you're superior to us...

314
00:25:55,283 --> 00:25:57,285
你不希望我挖出弗林的文件…
You wouldn't want me to dig up Flynn's file...

315
00:25:57,285 --> 00:26:00,121
并公布在泰晤士报可视终端上吧？
and read it up on a V.D.T. at the Times, would you?

316
00:26:00,121 --> 00:26:02,624
你不敢！
You wouldn't dare.

317
00:26:11,591 --> 00:26:14,969
- 嘿 - 嘿 加班了？
- Hi. - Hi. Working late?

318
00:26:14,969 --> 00:26:17,138
是的
Yeah.

319
00:26:22,101 --> 00:26:24,020
好的 过来
Okay, come here.

320
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:26,022
我让他用我的终端…
I am going to put him at my terminal.

321
00:26:26,022 --> 00:26:28,066
然后到楼上你的办公室找你
I am going to meet you in your office upstairs.

322
00:26:28,066 --> 00:26:31,736
别睡着了 如果我能启动创
Don't fall asleep. If and when I activate your Tron program,

323
00:26:31,736 --> 00:26:36,115
在迪林杰找到缺口前 你只有几分钟时间
you will only have a few minutes to use it before Dillinger catches the break in security.

324
00:26:36,115 --> 00:26:38,368
只要我们不到顶楼
As long as we stay off the top floor,

325
00:26:38,368 --> 00:26:40,787
迪林杰就不知道我们在这里
Dillinger will never know we have been in here.

326
00:26:40,787 --> 00:26:42,830
祝好运 hot shot
Good luck, hotshot.

327
00:27:04,685 --> 00:27:07,605
- 嗯哼 - 弗林
- Ahem. - Flynn.

328
00:27:07,605 --> 00:27:09,649
跟着你
After you.

329
00:27:32,046 --> 00:27:34,799
把那些有问题的程序清除出系统
Keep those programmers out of the system,

330
00:27:34,799 --> 00:27:37,969
把那些我要的汉语文件给我
and get me that Chinese language file I asked for.

331
00:27:37,969 --> 00:27:40,221
终点位置
End of line.

332
00:27:57,446 --> 00:28:00,324
- 你要支持我？ - 为什么？
- You are going to stick with me? - What for?

333
00:28:00,324 --> 00:28:02,618
你是唯一不需要帮助的 记得吗？
You're the one who never needed help, remember?

334
00:28:02,618 --> 00:28:06,122
